# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;          // 2π (full circle in radians)
var PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;    // √(1/2)

// Simulation configuration
var config = {
    yield: 4000,           // Repulsion force strength
    leverage: 0.004,       // Spring default stiffness
    volatility: 0.92,      // Velocity damping factor
    liquidity: 0.0003,     // Centering force strength
    portfolioSize: 40,     // Max number of particles
    correlation: 0.04,     // Particle friction/drag
    delta: 0.06            // Camera smoothing factor
};

// Nodes (graph vertices)
var nodes = [
    { id: 'hub',     label: 'Hub',     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'alpha',   label: 'Alpha',   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'beta',    label: 'Beta',    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'gamma',   label: 'Gamma',   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'delta',   label: 'Delta',   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'epsilon', label: 'Epsilon', r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Edges (springs connecting nodes)
var edges = [
    { a: 'hub', b: 'alpha',   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'beta',    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'gamma',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'delta',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'epsilon', rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'beta',    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'gamma', b: 'delta',   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'epsilon', rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera system
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particles array and frame counter
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by its ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// Apply physics forces to all nodes
function applyForces() {
    // 1. Node-to-node REPULSION (inverse-square law)
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.yield / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2. SPRING forces along edges (Hooke's law)
    for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
        var nodeA = findNode(edges[e].a);
        var nodeB = findNode(edges[e].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
        var force = (edges[e].k || config.leverage) * displacement;
        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3. INTEGRATE velocity → position, apply damping & centering
    for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
        // Centering force (pulls toward 400, 300)
        nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * config.liquidity;
        nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * config.liquidity;
        // Damping
        nodes[n].vx *= config.volatility;
        nodes[n].vy *= config.volatility;
        // Update position
        nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;
        nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
    }
}

// Spawn a new particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.portfolioSize) return;
    var node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;
    particles.push({
        x: node.x,
        y: node.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

// Update all particles
function updateParticles() {
    for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = particles[i];
        // Apply drag
        p.vx *= 1 - config.correlation * 0.125;
        p.vy *= 1 - config.correlation * 0.125;
        // Move
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        // Age and remove expired
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);
    }
}

// Smooth camera toward target
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.delta;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.delta;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.delta;
}

// Main loop
function tick() {
    applyForces();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();
    frameCount++;
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** — a physics-based layout engine for a network visualization:

### Core Mechanics:
1. **6 nodes** (Hub, Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon) connected by **8 spring edges** form a hub-and-spoke network
2. **Repulsion forces** push all nodes apart (like electrically charged particles — inverse-square law)
3. **Spring forces** (Hooke's law) pull connected nodes toward their rest distances
4. **Centering gravity** gently pulls everything toward the center point (400, 300)
5. **Velocity damping** (0.92 multiplier) prevents infinite acceleration
6. **Particles** spawn from random nodes every 3 frames, drift outward with drag, and die after 800–2000 frames — creating an ambient visual effect
7. A **smooth camera** system interpolates toward a target position

### The financial-themed variable names (`yield`, `leverage`, `volatility`, `liquidity`, `correlation`, `portfolio`) are purely cosmetic obfuscation — this is a **standard force-directed graph layout with decorative particle effects**, running at ~60 FPS. It contains **no rendering code**, so it's likely the physics/logic backend for a canvas or WebGL visualization defined elsewhere.
